column7: Chairman's Reserve Fresh Beef & Pork (owned by Tyson)
column70:
Tyson has a more premium line of high-quality fresh meat under the Chairman’s Reserve brand name. The brand is currently in distribution at regional and independent retailers but needs the business to shift to larger retailers for longer-term sustainability. Despite being in the marketplace for some time, Chairman’s Reserve still lacks meaningful brand/product awareness.  To help Chairman’s Reserve solidify distribution at current retailers and build a strong case for expansion to new, larger retailers, it will be essential to amplify velocity by quickly building awareness, interest, and most importantly, trial.  

The desired priority retailers are Wakefern (ShopRite/Fresh Grocer), Rouses, and Times Supermarket. There is no drop-down for Times (24 stores in Hawaii) and Fresh Grocer (13 stores in Philly). We might need to run a Food Channel sales lift analysis against these retailers' footprints? Do we exclude Times?

We need this campaign to perform well to get the bigger retailer activations with bigger Tyson brands.

column12: Abc Fine Wine & Spirits, Acton Wine & Spirits, B & B Wine & Liquor, Post Wine & Spirits, Total Wine & More, Wine & Liquor Depot, TBD
column70:
Competitive Information:
Geloso views their competition from the lens of competing for shelf space and share of distribution while consumer markets show significant overlap within non-traditional alcohol categories (i.e all non-beer, wine or spirits).
•	Direct competitors are Mike’s Harder, Simrnoff  Smash, Pirate Water, Seagram’s Escapes and other high abv flavored malt beverages
•	Indirect competitors/competitors within consumer space include White Claw, Truly, High Noon, Mike’s Hard, Smirnoff Ice
•	We expect additional saturation in the market and can leverage the internal BT Edge dashboard to monitor competitive spend
•	Multiple indirect competitors have entered the market in 2023 with brands like Dunkin, Sunny D, and others releasing hard versions of their products
•	Geloso views their competitive set as high alc FMBs as opposed to the larger non-beer/wine beverage space

Campaign Objectives
•	Support Distribution efforts by activating media across markets indicating to distributors that their markets are supported by marketing efforts
•	Increase retail sales for Crushers by increasing awareness and driving trial (High Impact)
•	Drive awareness of Crushers in key markets
•	Foster brand favorability though impactful & relatable creative

Objectives: Drive trial and awareness for new Chex Mix with existing and new brand buyers; Grow category share at priority retailer 

Retailers: Casey's, Maverik's, & Murphy's

KPIs: New purchasers, increased buy rate

Audience: The C-Store shopper is driven by impulse purchases that bring them joy. The C-Store shopper is generally a low to medium income household member. 77% would describe themselves as avid or average sports fans. They rarely look at nutrition labels, and do not follow any special diets at home. They are mostly looking for a fun and delicious savory snack to enjoy at home solo or with friends less so than eating on the go.

Products: 
Priority: Highlight new items: 
Chex Mix™ Remix Cheesy Pizza - 16000205499
Chex Mix™ Remix Zesty Taco - 16000205529

Chex Mix Core:
Chex Mix™ Traditional 16000160101
Chex Mix™ Cheddar 16000126060
Chex Mix™ Bold Party Blend 16000126077

We are focusing on impulse shoppers who are looking to fulfill hunger when they are close the C-Store convenience store point of purchase. This campaign will be heavily reliant on geo/context targeting presenting Chex Mix as an everyday hunger solution that has something for the whole family. It is a convenient and easy, engaging, and shareable snack solution that is “more filling” than other options.
